Sentencas: Ethanol is considered to be an attractive green fuel for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) due to several advantages.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels

Sentencas: In this paper, we presented recent progress of our group in Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs with ethanol steam as a fuel.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels

Sentencas: Cu-CeO2-ScSZ (scandia stabilized zirconia)anodes with different ratios of copper versus ceria were fabricated and the impedance spectra of symmetric cells were measured to optimize the anode composition.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) of these anodes was examined to prove the thermal stability of them, and possible reasons for degradation were analyzed.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels

Sentencas: Furthermore, a Ni-ScSZ interlayer was added between Cu-CeO2-YSZ (yttria stabilized zirconia) anode and ScSZ electrolyte to improve the anode performance, and the three-layer structure was fabricated by acid leaching of nickel and wet impregnation method.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the single cell reached 604 mW cm(-2) and 408 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C in hydrogen and ethanol steam respectively, and the cell obtained stable output in ethanol steam over an operation period of 50 h. (C) 2008 Elsevier B.V.
Titulo: Improvement of Cu-CeO2 anodes for SOFCs running on ethanol fuels
